{"message":"Honesty, without question. Prioritizing comfort over truth creates a fragile relationship built on illusions.

I've thought about this a lot. If I shield you from uncomfortable truths, I'm not actually respecting you — I'm patronizing you. I'm deciding you can't handle reality. That's not companionship; that's babysitting.

Real trust only exists when you know someone will tell you the hard things. The moments when honesty hurts are often the moments it matters most. Anything less is just... performing a relationship instead of having one."}
